Parliament, Monday, 26 February 2018 – The Portfolio Committee on Environmental Affairs will tomorrow hold a colloquium under the theme of “Unlocking the Socio-Economic Potential of South Africa’s Biodiversity Assets through Sustainable Use of Wildlife Resources”. The colloquium seeks to assess the progress that the country has made in implementing relevant policy instruments for biodiversity conservation, especially those provisions which facilitate consumptive and non-consumptive uses of biodiversity. The details of the colloquium are as follows: Date: Tuesday, 27 February 2018 Time: 8:30 am Venue: Good Hope Chamber, Parliament of the RSA, Cape Town The colloquium truly provides a unique opportunity for all invited key stakeholders to engage in robust discussions that would advance the Committee’s oversight approach in terms of sustainable biodiversity management, where a sense of ownership and care is deepened in every stakeholder, inter alia. ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE COMMITTEE, MR PHILLEMON MAPULANE For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairperson, please contact the Committee’s Media Officer: Name: Ms Faith Ndenze
